<div style="opacity: 1;"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-5"><path d="M8 2C6.89543 2 6 2.89543 6 4V14C6 15.1046 6.89543 16 8 16H14C15.1046 16 16 15.1046 16 14V4C16 2.89543 15.1046 2 14 2H8ZM7 4C7 3.44772 7.44772 3 8 3H14C14.5523 3 15 3.44772 15 4V14C15 14.5523 14.5523 15 14 15H8C7.44772 15 7 14.5523 7 14V4ZM4 6.00001C4 5.25973 4.4022 4.61339 5 4.26758V14.5C5 15.8807 6.11929 17 7.5 17H13.7324C13.3866 17.5978 12.7403 18 12 18H7.5C5.567 18 4 16.433 4 14.5V6.00001Z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div class="font-ligatures-none relative h-fit max-w-user-text-message whitespace-pre-wrap break-words px-4 py-2.5 squircle-16 bg-accent-250/60 dark:bg-accent-200 text-base self-end" data-content="user-message">I have some long lists of envirnoments that I am looking to subcatagorize. Think you can help?</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/ai-message" data-content="ai-message" data-testid="ai-message" aria-labelledby="wbZkD2DkUEBr8nV1RJKCV-author wbZkD2DkUEBr8nV1RJKCV-content-0" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative"><h6 id="wbZkD2DkUEBr8nV1RJKCV-author" class="sr-only" aria-label="Copilot said" data-copy="false">Copilot said</h6></div><div class="space-y-3 mt-3"><div class="group/ai-message-item space-y-3 break-words" id="wbZkD2DkUEBr8nV1RJKCV-content-0"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Absolutely — I can help you sort, cluster, and sub‑categorize long environment lists in a way that’s clean, logical, and reusable.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">To make this genuinely useful, I’ll outline a structure we can use, then you can drop in your first list and we’ll start shaping it.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">🗂️ How we can subcategorize environments</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Most large “environment” lists naturally break into a few major dimensions. Depending on what your lists look like, we can classify them by:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Biome type</strong> — forest, desert, tundra, grassland, aquatic, etc.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Climate</strong> — tropical, temperate, arid, polar, alpine.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Geography / landform</strong> — mountains, plains, canyons, wetlands, islands.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Human influence</strong> — urban, rural, industrial, abandoned, pristine wilderness.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Scale</strong> — micro‑environments, local habitats, regional ecosystems, global systems.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Function or narrative role</strong> — safe zones, hostile zones, resource‑rich areas, traversal areas (useful for worldbuilding or game design).</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">🧭 What I need from you</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Go ahead and paste <strong>one of your long lists</strong>, even if it’s messy or inconsistent. I’ll:</span></p><ol start="1" class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-5 marker:normal-nums marker:text-sm-strong"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Identify the natural categories that fit your specific items</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Propose a clean hierarchical structure</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Sort your items into those categories</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Flag any ambiguous or multi‑category items so you can decide how to treat them</span></p></li></ol><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Whenever you’re ready, drop in the first list and we’ll start shaping it.</span></p></div></div><div class="mt-3"><div class="flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out items-center group-focus-within/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-focus-within/ai-message:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message:opacity-100" data-copy="false" data-testid="message-item-reactions"><button aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" type="button" class="relative flex items-center text-foreground-800 fill-foreground-800 active:text-foreground-600 active:fill-foreground-600 dark:active:text-foreground-650 dark:active:fill-foreground-650 bg-transparent safe-hover:bg-black/5 active:bg-black/3 dark:safe-hover:bg-white/8 dark:active:bg-white/5 text-sm justify-center size-9 rounded-xl after:rounded-xl after:absolute after:inset-0 after:pointer-events-none after:border after:border-transparent after:contrast-more:border-2 outline-2 outl