ass="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine zones</strong> (Atmosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere — high‑elevation climate + terrain + vegetation)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine tundra</strong> (Atmosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine ridges</strong> (Atmosphere, Geosphere)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine meadows / meadowlands</strong> (Atmosphere, Biosphere, Geosphere)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine grasses / mosses</strong> (Atmosphere, Biosphere)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Atmosphere overlaps heavily with Geosphere (elevation), Hydrosphere (humidity, snow), and Biosphere (adaptations).</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🏙️ Anthrosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Human‑made or human‑modified environments.</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>abandoned settlements</strong> (Anthrosphere, Geosphere)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>abandoned zones</strong> (Anthrosphere, Geosphere)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>agriculture</strong>