4.61339 5 4.26758V14.5C5 15.8807 6.11929 17 7.5 17H13.7324C13.3866 17.5978 12.7403 18 12 18H7.5C5.567 18 4 16.433 4 14.5V6.00001Z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div class="font-ligatures-none relative h-fit max-w-user-text-message whitespace-pre-wrap break-words px-4 py-2.5 squircle-16 bg-accent-250/60 dark:bg-accent-200 text-base self-end" data-content="user-message">I don't understand some of the tags mostly the Atmosphere one. Like, abrupt cliffs (Geosphere, Atmosphere), alpine mosses (Biosphere, Atmosphere, Geosphere)</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/ai-message" data-content="ai-message" data-testid="ai-message" aria-labelledby="ynmCmxZZGNikZZE6SP6Gj-author ynmCmxZZGNikZZE6SP6Gj-content-0" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative"><h6 id="ynmCmxZZGNikZZE6SP6Gj-author" class="sr-only" aria-label="Copilot said" data-copy="false">Copilot said</h6></div><div class="space-y-3 mt-3"><div class="group/ai-message-item space-y-3 break-words" id="ynmCmxZZGNikZZE6SP6Gj-content-0"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">The confusion makes total sense — the Atmosphere tag only belongs on an item when <strong>air, climate, or atmospheric processes are actually part of what defines that feature</strong>. In the examples you pointed out, the Atmosphere tag wasn’t justified. Let’s clean that up and make the rule crisp.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌬️ When something <em>should</em> get the Atmosphere tag</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Use <strong>Atmosphere</strong> only when the feature involves:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">air movement (wind, turbulence, jets, drafts)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">weather (storms, fog, rain, snow, monsoons)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">climate conditions (temperature regimes, humidity, pressure)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">atmospheric chemistry (ozone, aerosols, smog)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">sky‑based phenomena (auroras, halos, lightning)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If the item is <strong>just a landform</strong> or <strong>just an organism</strong>, it does <em>not</em> get Atmosphere unless the air or climate is a defining part of its identity.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🪨 Why “abrupt cliffs” should NOT have Atmosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">A cliff is a <strong>geological landform</strong>.
Atmosphere doesn’t define it — erosion and weathering <em>affect</em> it, but that’s true for almost everything on Earth.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Correct tags:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>abrupt cliffs (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Only if you had something like “wind‑carved cliffs” or “fog‑shrouded cliffs” would Atmosphere be relevant.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌱 Why “alpine mosses” should NOT have Atmosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Alpine mosses are:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Biosphere</strong> (they’re living organisms)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Geosphere</strong> (they depend on rocky alpine substrates)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">They <em>occur</em> in a cold, thin‑air climate, but the climate doesn’t define the moss itself — it defines the <strong>alpine zone</strong>, not the organism.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Correct tags:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine mosses (Biosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If the item were “alpine climate” or “high‑altitude winds,” then Atmosphere would apply.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🧭 A clearer rule to avoid this confusion</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Think of it this way:</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">Atmosphere = “Is the air itself the feature?”</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If the answer is no, don’t tag it Atmosphere.</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">Geosphere = “Is this a physical landform or geological material?”</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If yes, it belongs there.</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">Biosphere = “Is this a living organism or biological system?”</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If yes, it belongs there.</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">Hydrosphere = “Is this water in any form?”</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If yes, it belongs there.</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5">Anthrosphere = “Is this human‑made or human‑modified?”</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If yes, it belongs there.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">✔️ Corrected versions of your examples</h2><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>abrupt cliffs (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine mosses (Biosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine grasses (Biosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>alpine ridges (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>air currents (Atmosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>acidic microclimates (Atmosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</strong> — because “microclimate” <em>is</em> an atmospheric condition</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>aeolian processes (Atmosphere, Geosphere)</strong> — because wind is the driver</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If you want, I can go back through the entire list we just sorted and clean up every Atmosphere tag so the logic is perfectly consistent.</span></p></div></div><div class="mt-3"><div class="flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out items-center group-focus-within/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-focus-within/ai-message:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message:opacity-100" data-copy="false" data-testid="message-item-reactions"><button aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" type="button" class="relative flex items-center text-foreground-800 fill-foreground-800 active:text-f