6768 13.6593L3.1605 16.8421L6.31982 16.1396C6.60164 16.0769 6.85976 15.9352 7.06391 15.731L15.0436 7.7513ZM2.5 3H11.3792L10.3792 4H2.5C2.22386 4 2 3.77614 2 3.5C2 3.22386 2.22386 3 2.5 3ZM2.5 6H8.37907L7.37902 7H2.5C2.22386 7 2 6.77614 2 6.5C2 6.22386 2.22386 6 2.5 6ZM2.5 9H5.37893L4.37888 10H2.5C2.22386 10 2 9.77614 2 9.5C2 9.22386 2.22386 9 2.5 9Z"></path></svg><span class="ms-1">Edit in a page</span></button></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/user-message space-y-1" id="bjjyULvNxrUF3DpgS1XTa-user-message" aria-labelledby="bjjyULvNxrUF3DpgS1XTa-user-message" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative space-y-3"><h5 class="sr-only" aria-label="You said" data-copy="false">You said</h5><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1"><div class="flex w-full items-start"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1"><div class="flex gap-2 justify-end"><div role="group" class="relative z-10 flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out group-focus-within/user-message:opacity-100 group-hover/user-message:opacity-100 items-center mt-auto" data-copy="false" data-testid="user-message-reactions"><div class="relative"><button aria-label="Copy message" type="button" class="relative flex items-center text-foreground-800 fill-foreground-800 active:text-foreground-600 active:fill-foreground-600 dark:active:text-foreground-650 dark:active:fill-foreground-650 bg-transparent safe-hover:bg-black/5 active:bg-black/3 dark:safe-hover:bg-white/8 dark:active:bg-white/5 text-sm justify-center size-9 rounded-xl after:rounded-xl after:absolute after:inset-0 after:pointer-events-none after:border after:border-transparent after:contrast-more:border-2 outline-2 outline-offset-1 focus-visible:z-[1] focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-stroke-900" data-testid="copy-user-message-button" data-spatial-navigation-autofocus="false" data-tooltip-state="closed"><div style="opacity: 1;"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-5"><path d="M8 2C6.89543 2 6 2.89543 6 4V14C6 15.1046 6.89543 16 8 16H14C15.1046 16 16 15.1046 16 14V4C16 2.89543 15.1046 2 14 2H8ZM7 4C7 3.44772 7.44772 3 8 3H14C14.5523 3 15 3.44772 15 4V14C15 14.5523 14.5523 15 14 15H8C7.44772 15 7 14.5523 7 14V4ZM4 6.00001C4 5.25973 4.4022 4.61339 5 4.26758V14.5C5 15.8807 6.11929 17 7.5 17H13.7324C13.3866 17.5978 12.7403 18 12 18H7.5C5.567 18 4 16.433 4 14.5V6.00001Z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div class="font-ligatures-none relative h-fit max-w-user-text-message whitespace-pre-wrap break-words px-4 py-2.5 squircle-16 bg-accent-250/60 dark:bg-accent-200 text-base self-end" data-content="user-message">First, let's look at our rules so I can kind of summarize and write them down</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/ai-message" data-content="ai-message" data-testid="ai-message" aria-labelledby="Az2tqZhWTwJ1oH9fvehmG-author Az2tqZhWTwJ1oH9fvehmG-content-0" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative"><h6 id="Az2tqZhWTwJ1oH9fvehmG-author" class="sr-only" aria-label="Copilot said" data-copy="false">Copilot said</h6></div><div class="space-y-3 mt-3"><div class="group/ai-message-item space-y-3 break-words" id="Az2tqZhWTwJ1oH9fvehmG-content-0"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Here’s a clean, accurate, and <em>usable</em> summary of the rules we’ve been following — the ones that make this whole classification system work smoothly and consistently. These are written so you can literally copy/paste them into your notes as your “official” tagging rules.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌍 Core Principle</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Every item can belong to <strong>one or more</strong> Earth system spheres.
You tag an item based on <strong>what it </strong><em><strong>is</strong></em>, not what influences it.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌬️ Atmosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag <strong>only</strong> when the feature <em>is</em> air, weather, climate, or atmospheric optics.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Atmosphere applies to:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">air movement (winds, drafts, currents)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">weather (storms, fog, rain, snow, droughts)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">climate conditions (heat, cold, humidity, seasons)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">atmospheric phenomena (halos, arcs, glare)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">atmospheric chemistry (moisture, aerosols)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Atmosphere does <strong>not</strong> apply just because climate affects the feature.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fog (Atmosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>cold snaps (Atmosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>boundary‑layer rolls (Atmosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fog‑fed forests (Atmosphere, Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>extreme heat (Atmosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🏙️ Anthrosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is <strong>human‑made or human‑modified</strong>.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Anthrosphere applies to:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">settlements, ruins, abandoned structures</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">agriculture, croplands, farmlands</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">canals, constructed waterways</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">deforested slopes</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">fire rings, managed burns</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">fragmented habitats (human-caused)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>constructed waterways (Anthrosphere, Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>farmlands (Anthrosphere, Biosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>abandoned settlements (Anthrosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌱 Biosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is <strong>alive</strong>, biological, or an ecological community.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Biosphere applies to:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">plants, trees, shrubs, grasses</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">animals, insects, birds, fish</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">microbial life, extremophiles</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">habitats, vegetation types</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">organic matter (litter, root mats)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>elk (Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>cushion plants (Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>forest understory (Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>epiphytes (Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>extremophile microbes (Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🪨 Geosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is <strong>land, rock, soil, terrain, or geological process</strong>.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Geosphere applies to:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">landforms (cliffs, dunes, valleys, ridges)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">rock types (basalt, chalk, crystal outcrops)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">geomorphology (erosion, deposition, turbation)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">soil types (cryptobiotic soils, fertile soils)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">extraterrestrial terrain (craters, alien landscapes)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>eskers (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>erosion‑dominated landforms (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>crystalline outcrops (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>flat‑topped mountains (Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">💧 Hydrosphere</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is <strong>water</strong>, depends on water, or is a water‑formed system.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Hydrosphere applies to:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">lakes, rivers, streams, wetlands</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">oceans, seas, bays, fjords</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">groundwater, aquifers, springs</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">brackish water, evaporative basins</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">deep‑sea zones, vents</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">water chemistry (brine, caustic water)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>estuaries (Hydrosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>ephemeral lakes (Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>floating reed beds (Hydrosphere, Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>deep sea vents (Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌀 Other</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Use only when the item <strong>does not map to any physical sphere</strong>.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">This is rare.
Examples include:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">astronomical objects (comets, extra‑solar objects)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">conceptual or non‑physical terms (if they appear)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>comets (Atmosphere, Other)</strong> — atmospheric entry + non‑Earth object</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>extra‑solar objects (Other)</strong></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🧭 Multi‑Tagging Rules</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">A feature gets <strong>every sphere that directly defines it</strong>, not just the primary one.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fog‑fed oases (Atmosphere, Hydrosphere, Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>crystal bogs (Hydrosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>constructed waterways (Anthrosphere, Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>forest wetlands (Hydrosphere, Biosphere, Geosphere)</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If water, land, and life are all essential → tag all three.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">❌ What <em>not</em> to do</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">These are the mistakes we’ve avoided:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Atmosphere just because climate influences the feature.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Hydrosphere unless water is actually present.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Biosphere for dead rock or terrain.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Anthrosphere unless humans built or altered it.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t force items into a single category when they naturally span several.</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">✔️ The system in one sentence</h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Tag each item by what it </strong><em><strong>is</strong></em><strong>, and include every sphere that directly defines its nature or structure.</strong></span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If you want, I can turn this into a polished reference sheet or a compact rule card you can keep beside you while we continue.</span></p></div></div><div class="mt-3"><div class="flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out items-center group-focus-within/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-focus-within/ai-message:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message:opacity-100" data-copy="false" data-testid="message-item-reactions"><button aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" type="button" class="relative flex items-center text-foreground-800 fill-foreground-800 active:text-foreground-600 active:fill-foreground-600 dark:active:text-foreground-650 dark:active:fill-foreground-650 bg-transparent safe-hover:bg-black/5 active:bg-black/3 dark:safe-hover:bg-white/8 dark:active:bg-white/5 text-sm justify-center size-9 rounded-xl after:rounded-xl after:absolute after:inset-0 after:pointer-events-none after:border after:border-transparent after:contrast-more:border-2 outline-2 outline-offset-1 focus-visible:z-[1] focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-stroke-900" data-testid="message-thumbs-up-button" data-spatial-navigation-autofocus="false" data-tooltip-state="closed"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-5"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M10.7002 2.01074C11.0952 2.06005 11.4528 2.2785 11.6768 2.61426C12.2133 3.41901 12.5 4.36484 12.5 5.33203V5.95312C12.5 6.64737 12.3947 7.33709 12.1904 8H15.6914C16.9663 8 18 9.03369 18 10.3086C18 10.471 17.9832 10.6331 17.9492 10.792L16.7432 16.4189C16.5456 17.3411 15.7302 18 14.7871 18H9.