justify-center size-9 rounded-xl after:rounded-xl after:absolute after:inset-0 after:pointer-events-none after:border after:border-transparent after:contrast-more:border-2 outline-2 outline-offset-1 focus-visible:z-[1] focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-stroke-900" data-testid="copy-user-message-button" data-spatial-navigation-autofocus="false" data-tooltip-state="closed"><div style="opacity: 1;"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-5"><path d="M8 2C6.89543 2 6 2.89543 6 4V14C6 15.1046 6.89543 16 8 16H14C15.1046 16 16 15.1046 16 14V4C16 2.89543 15.1046 2 14 2H8ZM7 4C7 3.44772 7.44772 3 8 3H14C14.5523 3 15 3.44772 15 4V14C15 14.5523 14.5523 15 14 15H8C7.44772 15 7 14.5523 7 14V4ZM4 6.00001C4 5.25973 4.4022 4.61339 5 4.26758V14.5C5 15.8807 6.11929 17 7.5 17H13.7324C13.3866 17.5978 12.7403 18 12 18H7.5C5.567 18 4 16.433 4 14.5V6.00001Z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div class="font-ligatures-none relative h-fit max-w-user-text-message whitespace-pre-wrap break-words px-4 py-2.5 squircle-16 bg-accent-250/60 dark:bg-accent-200 text-base self-end" data-content="user-message">please do</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/ai-message" data-content="ai-message" data-testid="ai-message" aria-labelledby="ZLbV9ZgmZdMYmYgDMLtCV-author ZLbV9ZgmZdMYmYgDMLtCV-content-0" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative"><h6 id="ZLbV9ZgmZdMYmYgDMLtCV-author" class="sr-only" aria-label="Copilot said" data-copy="false">Copilot said</h6></div><div class="space-y-3 mt-3"><div class="group/ai-message-item space-y-3 break-words" id="ZLbV9ZgmZdMYmYgDMLtCV-content-0"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Here is a polished, compact, and ready‑to‑use <strong>reference sheet</strong> for your classification system. It captures every rule we’ve been following, written so you can keep it beside you as you continue building your environment taxonomy.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h1 class="text-2xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-6">🌍 <strong>Environmental Sphere Tagging Reference Sheet</strong></h1><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">This system classifies any environmental feature using <strong>five Earth system spheres</strong>, with <strong>multi‑tagging allowed</strong>.
Each item is tagged according to <strong>what it </strong><em><strong>is</strong></em>, not what influences it.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌬️ <strong>Atmosphere</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature <em>is</em> air, weather, climate, or atmospheric optics.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Weather: fog, storms, rain, snow, droughts</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Climate conditions: heat, cold, humidity, seasons</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Air movement: winds, drafts, downbursts</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Atmospheric phenomena: halos, arcs, glare</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Atmospheric moisture: evaporation, atmospheric rivers</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Does NOT include:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Landforms shaped by climate</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Organisms adapted to climate</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Terrain influenced by weather</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>fog (Atmosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>cold snaps (Atmosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>boundary‑layer rolls (Atmosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>extreme heat (Atmosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🏙️ <strong>Anthrosphere</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is human‑made or human‑modified.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Settlements, ruins, abandoned structures</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Agriculture, croplands, farmlands</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Canals, constructed waterways</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Deforested slopes</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Fire rings, managed burns</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Habitat fragmentation caused by humans</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>constructed waterways (Anthrosphere, Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>farmlands (Anthrosphere, Biosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>abandoned settlements (Anthrosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌱 <strong>Biosphere</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is alive, biological, or an ecological community.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Plants, trees, shrubs, grasses</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Animals, insects, birds, fish</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Microbial life, extremophiles</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Habitats, vegetation types</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Organic matter (litter, roots, mats)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>elk (Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>epiphytes (Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>forest understory (Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>extremophile microbes (Biosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🪨 <strong>Geosphere</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is land, rock, soil, or geological process.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Landforms: cliffs, dunes, valleys, ridges</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Rock types: basalt, chalk, crystal outcrops</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Geomorphology: erosion, deposition, turbation</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Soil types: cryptobiotic soils, fertile soils</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Extraterrestrial terrain: craters, alien landscapes</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>eskers (Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>erosion‑dominated landforms (Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>crystalline outcrops (Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>flat‑topped mountains (Geosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">💧 <strong>Hydrosphere</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Tag when the feature is water, depends on water, or is a water‑formed system.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Lakes, rivers, streams, wetlands</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Oceans, seas, bays, fjords</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Groundwater, aquifers, springs</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Brackish water, evaporative basins</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Deep‑sea zones, vents</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Water chemistry: brine, caustic water</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>estuaries (Hydrosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>ephemeral lakes (Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>floating reed beds (Hydrosphere, Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>deep sea vents (Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌀 <strong>Other</strong></h2><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Use only when the item does <strong>not</strong> map to any physical sphere.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Includes:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Astronomical objects</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Non‑physical concepts</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>comets (Atmosphere, Other)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>extra‑solar objects (Other)</em></span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h1 class="text-2xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-6">🔗 <strong>Multi‑Tagging Rules</strong></h1><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">A feature receives <strong>every sphere that directly defines it</strong>.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Examples:</strong></span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>fog‑fed oases (Atmosphere, Hydrosphere, Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>crystal bogs (Hydrosphere, Geosphere, Biosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>constructed waterways (Anthrosphere, Hydrosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><em>forest wetlands (Hydrosphere, Biosphere, Geosphere)</em></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If water, land, and life are all essential → tag all three.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h1 class="text-2xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-6">❌ <strong>Common Mistakes to Avoid</strong></h1><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Atmosphere just because climate influences the feature.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Hydrosphere unless water is actually present.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Biosphere for dead rock or terrain.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t tag Anthrosphere unless humans built or altered it.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Don’t force items into a single category when they naturally span several.</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h1 class="text-2xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-6">✔️ <strong>One‑Sentence Summary</strong></h1><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Tag each item by what it </strong><em><strong>is</strong></em><strong>, and include every sphere that directly defines its nature or structure.</strong></span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt