 6H8.37907L7.37902 7H2.5C2.22386 7 2 6.77614 2 6.5C2 6.22386 2.22386 6 2.5 6ZM2.5 9H5.37893L4.37888 10H2.5C2.22386 10 2 9.77614 2 9.5C2 9.22386 2.22386 9 2.5 9Z"></path></svg><span class="ms-1">Edit in a page</span></button></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/user-message space-y-1" id="bgPJZYcNUZtsznudeqpoM-user-message" aria-labelledby="bgPJZYcNUZtsznudeqpoM-user-message" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative space-y-3"><h5 class="sr-only" aria-label="You said" data-copy="false">You said</h5><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1"><div class="flex w-full items-start"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1"><div class="flex gap-2 justify-end"><div role="group" class="relative z-10 flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out group-focus-within/user-message:opacity-100 group-hover/user-message:opacity-100 items-center" data-copy="false" data-testid="user-message-reactions"><div class="relative"><button aria-label="Copy message" type="button" class="relative flex items-center text-foreground-800 fill-foreground-800 active:text-foreground-600 active:fill-foreground-600 dark:active:text-foreground-650 dark:active:fill-foreground-650 bg-transparent safe-hover:bg-black/5 active:bg-black/3 dark:safe-hover:bg-white/8 dark:active:bg-white/5 text-sm justify-center size-9 rounded-xl after:rounded-xl after:absolute after:inset-0 after:pointer-events-none after:border after:border-transparent after:contrast-more:border-2 outline-2 outline-offset-1 focus-visible:z-[1] focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-stroke-900" data-testid="copy-user-message-button" data-spatial-navigation-autofocus="false" data-tooltip-state="closed"><div style="opacity: 1;"><svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="size-5"><path d="M8 2C6.89543 2 6 2.89543 6 4V14C6 15.1046 6.89543 16 8 16H14C15.1046 16 16 15.1046 16 14V4C16 2.89543 15.1046 2 14 2H8ZM7 4C7 3.44772 7.44772 3 8 3H14C14.5523 3 15 3.44772 15 4V14C15 14.5523 14.5523 15 14 15H8C7.44772 15 7 14.5523 7 14V4ZM4 6.00001C4 5.25973 4.4022 4.61339 5 4.26758V14.5C5 15.8807 6.11929 17 7.5 17H13.7324C13.3866 17.5978 12.7403 18 12 18H7.5C5.567 18 4 16.433 4 14.5V6.00001Z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div class="font-ligatures-none relative h-fit max-w-user-text-message whitespace-pre-wrap break-words px-4 py-2.5 squircle-16 bg-accent-250/60 dark:bg-accent-200 text-base self-end" data-content="user-message">yes please</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-tabster="{&quot;groupper&quot;:{&quot;tabbability&quot;:2},&quot;focusable&quot;:{}}" class="group/ai-message" data-content="ai-message" data-testid="ai-message" aria-labelledby="WuUgFbwoa49XcRjXzZVJb-author WuUgFbwoa49XcRjXzZVJb-content-0" tabindex="0" role="article"><div class="relative"><h6 id="WuUgFbwoa49XcRjXzZVJb-author" class="sr-only" aria-label="Copilot said" data-copy="false">Copilot said</h6></div><div class="space-y-3 mt-3"><div class="group/ai-message-item space-y-3 break-words" id="WuUgFbwoa49XcRjXzZVJb-content-0"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">A uniform naming system works best when it’s simple, predictable, and applies cleanly across thousands of entries. The patterns you’re already using make that possible, so the goal now is to lock them in as <strong>formal rules</strong> you can apply everywhere.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌍 Core Naming Rules for Your Environmental Taxonomy</h2><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>1. Always use the plural form for countable features</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">This prevents duplicates and keeps the list searchable and consistent.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Use:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>snow caps</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost heaves</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>bog pools</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>grasslands</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>dune fields</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>crystal outcrops</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Avoid:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">snow cap</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">frost heave</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">bog pool</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">grassland (unless referring to the biome category itself)</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>Exception:</strong>  
Use singular only when the concept is inherently singular or uncountable:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">bedrock</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">permafrost</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">tundra</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">groundwater</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">evaporation</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>2. Use hyphens for compound adjectives modifying a noun</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">This is the biggest consistency win.
If the phrase describes a noun directly, hyphenate it.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost‑covered terrain</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>snow‑covered peaks</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>wind‑shaped dunes</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fire‑adapted species</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>cold‑region landscapes</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fog‑fed forests</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>salt‑crusted flats</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">These read cleanly and avoid ambiguity.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>3. Use spaces when the phrase is a noun phrase, not a modifier</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If the phrase stands alone as a concept, not modifying a noun, keep it spaced.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>snow caps</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>ice fields</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>grass fires</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>fog banks</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost heaves</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">These are nouns, not adjectives.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>4. When both forms exist (e.g., frost covered vs. frost‑covered), choose the hyphenated adjective form</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Your dataset overwhelmingly uses these as descriptors of terrain, vegetation, or landforms.</span></p><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">So the standardized form is:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost‑covered</strong> (when modifying something)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost‑covered terrain</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost‑covered plains</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>frost‑covered hollows</strong></span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If you ever list it alone as a concept (rare), you could use “frost covered,” but your structure almost never uses standalone descriptors.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>5. When in doubt, follow these defaults</strong></h3><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If it’s describing another feature → <strong>hyphenate</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If it’s a standalone feature → <strong>pluralize</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If it’s a material or continuous surface → <strong>singular</strong></span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If it’s a biome or vegetation type → <strong>plural</strong> unless it’s a category name</span></p></li></ul><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">Examples:</span></p><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>lava fields</strong> → plural</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>permafrost</strong> → singular</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>tundra</strong> → singular</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>wetlands</strong> → plural</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>forest floor</strong> → singular (a single conceptual layer)</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap"><strong>forest floors</strong> → plural (multiple instances)</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🌱 Applying the rules to your examples</h2><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>snow cap / snow caps</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">→ <strong>snow caps</strong> (plural noun)</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>frost covered / frost‑covered</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">→ <strong>frost‑covered</strong> (compound adjective)</span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>frost covered terrain</strong></h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">→ <strong>frost‑covered terrain</strong></span></p><h3 class="text-lg-strong pb-1 [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5"><strong>frost covered</strong> (standalone)</h3><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">→ Rare, but would be <strong>frost covered</strong> (no hyphen)
However, your dataset almost never uses standalone descriptors, so the hyphenated form is the standard.</span></p><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><h2 class="text-xl-medium [&amp;:not(:first-child)]:pt-3.5 pb-1">🧭 Why this system works</h2><ul class="relative list-outside marker:text-foreground-750 dark:marker:text-foreground-600 flex flex-col ms-4 px-1"><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">It keeps your list searchable and sortable.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">It prevents duplicates like “snow cap” and “snow caps.”</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">It keeps descriptors consistent across thousands of entries.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">It matches scientific writing conventions in ecology, geology, and climatology.</span></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">It scales cleanly as your list grows.</span></p></li></ul><div class="relative pb-6 w-full after:border-b after:border-stroke-300 after:w-full after:absolute after:mt-3"></div><p><span class="font-ligatures-none whitespace-pre-wrap">If you want, I can now go through your existing entries and normalize all names to match these rules so your entire dataset is uniform.</span></p></div></div><div class="mt-3"><div class="flex opacity-0 transition-opacity duration-300 ease-in-out items-center group-focus-within/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message-item:opacity-100 group-focus-within/ai-message:opacity-100 group-hover/ai-message:opacity-100" data-copy="false" data-testid="message-item-reactions"><button aria-label="Good response" aria-pressed="false" type="button" clas